<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8376> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8376" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 85, Promagistrates." ;
	dprr:hasID 8376 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7256> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7256" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis. In MRR 2.437, and Index, 555-556? refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.319, no. 311, 106 B.C. Procos. 85. He was governor of Macedonia rather than Illyria in 85 (see MRR 2.58, 59, note 2; Badian, Studies 80-81; Sumner, Orators 104). On his priesthood, see below, on L. Cornelius Sulla (392). Cos. 88, 80. Diodorus (38.16) also mentions his attempt to start a rising against Sulla in his consulship (see MRR 2.62, 65, note 1).\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7256 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4110> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4110" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Quinct. 24; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 54f., 130, 484f.; Tac. Hist. 3.72; App. BC 1.82; Flor. 2.9.18; Obseq. 57; Eutrop. 5.7; Chr. 354 (Asiatico II et Pulbo); Fast. Hyd. (Scipione et Narbone), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Scipio, Cic. Verr. 2.1.37." ;
	dprr:hasID 4110 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4088> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4088" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Carried on war with Illyrian and Thracian tribesmen in Illyricum, including the Maedi, who in late 85 or early 84 raided even Delphi (App. Illyr. 5; cf. Plut. Numa 12.6-8, a propos of the war with the Gauls in 387; Jerome, Chr. ad ann. 84, p. 151 Helm; see Fouilles de Delphes 3.54, and 55)." ;
	dprr:hasID 4088 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4087> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4087" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "2 A solution for the knotty problem of the date of Scipio's command in Illyricum (or Macedonia) has been suggested by G. Daux (Delphes aux IIe et au Ier siecle 392-397). As against Pomtow (RhM 51 [1896] 329 ff., esp. 364-376), he keeps the Ms reading in Appian #, and accepts in Plutarch the emendation of # to # in # (see A.-J. Reinach, BCH 34 L 1910] 249-330, esp. 313-32 1; Münzer, RE, Supb. 3.26 1). Eusebius's synchronism of the burning of the temple at Delphi (exaggerated) and that of the Capitolium in Rome falls into place. It remains difficult to explain Appian's reference to 32 years since the first conflicts between Romans and Celts. Perhaps his number should be emended to 302, i. e., since 387 B. C., otherwise it may refer to the triumph of Metellus Delmaticus 32 years before in 117. For earlier discussions, see Gäbler, RE s. v. \"Makedonia,\" 766 (dates Scipio in 88); and Zippel, Römische Herrschaft in Illyricum 190." ;
	dprr:hasID 4087 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3998> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3998" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "L. Cornelius Scipio Asiagenus succeeded M. Aemilius Scaurus. Fast. Sac., CIL 12.1, p. 60-ILS 9338, no. 4. His cognomen in Fast. Cap. for 83 is Asiaticus (Degrassi 54f.)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3998 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3874> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3874" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In command, along with Acilius, at Aesernia, whence he escaped in disguise (App. BC 1.41; see above on Acilius, and note 13)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3874 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10281> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10281" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/26> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "C.60 (praefectus oppidi or legatus, MRR has as a possible legatus (lieutentant))" ;
	dprr:hasID 10281 .
